==English==
===Noun===
'''boy band''' (''plural'' '''boy bands''')

#A [[pop group]] whose members are all (usually attractive) young men.

====Usage note====
*'''Boy band''' is sometimes used as a disparaging term for a mainstream pop group made up of young men, implying that the group members are successful on the basis of their looks and sex appeal rather than their musical ability.

